Quote:  <i>F. Solandri, Hook.f</i>. ... A lofty forest-tree 40-60 ft. high; ... bark black ... in old trees ... pale and smooth on young ones; ... Leaves ... clothed with an appressed greyish-white pubescence beneath ... usually in hilly or mountain districts. ... <i>Tawhai; Tawhai-rauriki; Black-birch; White-birch. </i>... Wood pale-red, often streaked with black, not durable ...
